{"TopicId":175380,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"RCS on HubMax?","CreatedByName":"Gilead","CreatedById":184696,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-27T20:24:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gilead","CreatedById":184696,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-27T20:24:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi everyone!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am currently in the process of designing a space station. I use\u00A0a\u00A0\u003Cem\u003ERockomax HubMax Multi-Point Connector\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0as core. I wanted to add\u00A0\u003Cem\u003ERV-105 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Thruster Blocks\u003C/em\u003E on the \u003Cem\u003EHubMax\u003C/em\u003E, specifically 8 \u003Cem\u003ERV-105\u003C/em\u003E on the 8 triangle-shaped faces of the \u003Cem\u003EHubMax\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was the idea, but when I try to add \u003Cem\u003ERV-105s\u003C/em\u003E on the \u003Cem\u003EHubMax\u003C/em\u003E, they won\u0027t attach! Is it normal behavior? Is there a way to circumvent this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for reading me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-27T20:24:28Z\u0022 title=\u002205/27/2018 08:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 27, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Gilead\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-27T23:14:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm. It does seem to be true that the Hubmax is not surface attachable. So it\u0027s normal behavior. I\u0027m not sure it\u0027s intended though -- I can\u0027t think of any good reason why it should be set that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo circumvent it, you need to change the attachrules in the \u0022StationHub.cfg\u0022 file to say\u00A0attachRules = 1,0,1,1,0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gilead","CreatedById":184696,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-27T23:29:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you very much! It works almost fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlmost, because if I put the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E on the circuclar parts of the HubMax, it behaves normally, but if I try to put it on the little triangles it goes trough. Nothing that can\u0027t be solve with a little use of the move and rotate tools.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo problem solved. Thank you again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-28T00:11:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223387516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527462852\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n56 minutes ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t think of any good reason why it should be set that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223387525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527463781\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gilead\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, Gilead said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif I try to put it on the little triangles it goes trough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s probably the reason. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kesa","CreatedById":130333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-30T13:55:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBear in mind that torque is proportional to the distance from the center to the place a thrust is applied. In other words, \u003Cstrong\u003Ethe core of your station is the worst possible place to put \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters\u003C/strong\u003E. It is however, the best place to put reaction wheel, to limit the structural stress put on the station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-30T13:56:32Z\u0022 title=\u002205/30/2018 01:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Kesa\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-30T14:47:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy work around for this has been to slap an Advanced Inline Stabilizer, Z-1k, or FL-R25, on the open faces of the HubMax, and attach the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E blocks to those, usually the reaction wheels. Then when I use them I\u0027m tending to design some high\u00A0mass module movers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-31T17:33:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223389299\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527691667\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277368\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steuben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/30/2018 at 9:47 AM, steuben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nZ-1k\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood idea. And you\u2019ll have lots or power to boot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}